00:22:45.990 --> 00:22:47.620
of like a tamale or
something, you know.

00:22:47.620 --> 00:22:53.530
It's some kind of way in which
-- so this mix -- it makes sense.

00:22:53.530 --> 00:22:57.210
The Philippines was colonized
not from continental Spain

00:22:57.210 --> 00:22:59.940
but from New Spain, from Mexico.

00:22:59.940 --> 00:23:03.100
And so to have -- and
because of that --

00:23:03.100 --> 00:23:08.770
the Manila-Acapulco route with the
silver that was being moved back

00:23:08.770 --> 00:23:11.170
and forth -- I mean, we're
talking hundreds of years.

00:23:11.170 --> 00:23:13.500
And so that's, you know,
it would make sense

00:23:13.500 --> 00:23:20.000
that there would be these
intersections of culture,

00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:25.680
whether it be language,
or religion, or food.

00:23:25.680 --> 00:23:28.230 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Roberto Salazar: Aside from that
